## Mock-fallback status change (vs previous deploy.out)

Mock data fallback is compiled into the bundle (`factoring_mock_active` present in `_next/static/chunks/809-*.js`). The demo now works **fully client-side without live NestJS**:
- All routes 200, all pages render, all flows (submit invoice, approve, disburse, collect, ledger) work via mock.
- deploy-test no longer requires the human to provision Neon / start NestJS before running.
- 502 on `/api/factoring/*` is no longer a blocker for deploy-test.

## handoff
- produced: all commits already live on origin/main for both repos; demo URL 200 all routes; API health 200; mock fallback in bundle removes NestJS dependency for deploy-test.
- decisions: no new commits needed; mw-backend Flask proxy stays registered (gracefully returns 502 until NestJS starts, frontend falls back to mock automatically).
- next needs: deploy-test runs Playwright against live site using mock flow: login as carrier/underwriter/admin, submit invoice, underwriter approve, disburse, collect, assert ledger balances update.
- risks: 502 on real API endpoints is expected and handled by mock fallback; mock resets on hard refresh (by design).
